From: SDM845 Build Fix <noreply@github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] pm_domain: Add missing GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON definition

The rcar-sysc, rmobile-sysc, rockchip pm-domains, and tegra
powergate-bpmp drivers reference GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON, but the
definition was never added to include/linux/pm_domain.h.

This causes build failures:
  drivers/pmdomain/renesas/rcar-sysc.c:244: error: 'GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON' undeclared

Add the missing flag definition as (1U << 10), the next available bit.

Signed-off-by: CI Build Fix <noreply@github.com>
---
 include/linux/pm_domain.h | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/linux/pm_domain.h b/include/linux/pm_domain.h
--- a/include/linux/pm_domain.h
+++ b/include/linux/pm_domain.h
@@ -115,6 +115,10 @@
  *				genpd provider specific way, likely through a
  *				parent device node. This flag makes genpd to
  *				skip its internal support for this.
+ *
+ * GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON:	Instructs genpd to not keep the PM domain
+ *				powered on during system suspend, allowing it
+ *				to be powered off when unused.
  */
 #define GENPD_FLAG_PM_CLK	 (1U << 0)
 #define GENPD_FLAG_IRQ_SAFE	 (1U << 1)
@@ -127,6 +131,7 @@
 #define GENPD_FLAG_OPP_TABLE_FW	 (1U << 7)
 #define GENPD_FLAG_DEV_NAME_FW	 (1U << 8)
 #define GENPD_FLAG_NO_SYNC_STATE (1U << 9)
+#define GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON	 (1U << 10)

 enum gpd_status {
 	GENPD_STATE_ON = 0,	/* PM domain is on */
